  <h1>Professional LG Dryer Overheating Repair Service Los Angeles County</h1>
  <p>When your LG dryer runs dangerously hot or shuts down mid-cycle, you need immediate professional repair to prevent fire hazards and protect your home. Our experienced technicians diagnose and fix LG dryer overheating issues throughout Los Angeles County with same-day service and a one-year warranty on all work.</p>

<h2>Critical Warning Signs Your LG Dryer Is Overheating</h2>
<p>The first thing we tell clients is that an overheating dryer isn't just an inconvenience—it's a genuine fire hazard that requires immediate attention. Nine times out of ten, the warning signs are unmistakable once you know what to look for.</p>
<p>Your LG dryer will shut down unexpectedly during cycles, often displaying error codes like tE1, tE2, or d80.</p>
<figure class="article-img article-img--square">
  <img src="/images/symptoms/lg-dryer-overheating-error-code-new.webp"
       alt="LG dryer display showing tE1 error code — thermal sensor overheating shutdown"
       width="600" height="600" loading="lazy" />
  <figcaption>tE1 error — internal sensors detected dangerous
  temperatures and triggered emergency shutdown to protect
  the machine and your home</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>The exterior cabinet becomes burning hot to touch, especially around the top and back panels. Clothes come out scorching hot even on low heat settings, and synthetic fabrics may show heat damage or melting. You'll notice the laundry room temperature rises dramatically during operation.</p>
<p>Other telltale signs include longer drying times as the unit struggles with thermal protection kicks, a burning smell that doesn't dissipate after cleaning the lint filter, and excessive lint buildup despite regular maintenance. In Burbank and Pasadena homes, we frequently see these symptoms worsen during summer months when ambient temperatures stress already compromised thermal components.</p>
<p>The moment you notice any combination of these symptoms, turn off the dryer immediately and call our emergency line. Continuing to operate an overheating LG dryer risks permanent damage to expensive components and creates serious fire danger for your family.</p>
<h3>Emergency Shutdown Indicators</h3>
<p>When your LG dryer displays error codes tE1 through tE4, the internal sensors have detected dangerous temperature levels exceeding safe operating limits. These codes specifically indicate thermal sensor malfunctions or blocked airflow causing heat buildup. The dryer automatically enters protective shutdown mode, but the underlying problem requires professional diagnosis. Our technicians carry the proper diagnostic equipment to test thermal sensors and high-limit switches that trigger these emergency codes.</p>
<h3>Physical Heat Damage Warning Signs</h3>
<p>Clothes emerging with scorch marks, particularly on synthetic blends and delicate fabrics, signal that your dryer's temperature regulation system has failed completely.</p>
