  for multiple cycles</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>We've seen cases in Beverly Hills where expensive garments suffered hundreds of dollars in damage because homeowners ignored early overheating symptoms. The burning odor that persists even after thorough cleaning indicates internal components are literally cooking from excessive heat exposure.</p>
<h2>Our Professional LG Dryer Overheating Repair Process</h2>
<p>When you call our emergency line at (323) 990-7550, we'll schedule same-day service and walk you through safe shutdown procedures until our technician arrives. Our systematic diagnostic approach identifies the root cause quickly, saving you time and preventing misdiagnosis that leads to unnecessary part replacements.</p>
<p>Our technician begins with comprehensive thermal testing using calibrated temperature probes at multiple points throughout the dryer's airflow system. We test the exhaust temperature, internal drum heat levels, and component temperatures under controlled conditions. This reveals whether the problem stems from airflow restriction, failed thermal components, or electrical issues.</p>
<p>Next, we inspect the entire ventilation pathway from the lint screen through the external exhaust vent. Blocked or damaged ductwork causes 60% of overheating issues we encounter in Glendale and Torrance installations. We use specialized tools to clear blockages and verify proper airflow velocity.</p>
