The exact cost depends on which thermal components require replacement and the complexity of accessing them in your specific LG model. Simple thermal fuse replacement represents the lower end of our pricing range, while heating element replacement combined with thermostat replacement approaches the higher end. Our service call fee gets waived when you proceed with repairs, and we provide transparent parts pricing by showing you the component costs on supplier websites.

For complex cases requiring unit removal or special tools, costs may reach $350-450, but this still represents substantial savings compared to purchasing new equipment. About 50% of our overheating service calls end as diagnostic-only visits costing $65-120, where we identify minor issues like loose connections or error code resets that restore normal operation.

Our flexible pricing policy means clients benefit when parts are available from our warehouse inventory purchased at lower prices, and returning customers receive 10% labor discounts. We also work with clients to prioritize repairs when multiple components need attention, spreading costs across service visits when budget considerations apply.</p>
<h3>Component Cost Breakdown</h3>
<p>Thermal fuses typically cost $25-45, high-limit thermostats range $30-60, and heating elements cost $80-150 depending on your LG model series. Labor charges cover proper installation, calibration, and testing to ensure reliable operation. Complex repairs involving <a href="/repairs/lg-dryer-drum-roller-replacement/">drum roller replacement</a> may require additional time for complete disassembly, but prevent future overheating caused by mechanical binding.</p>
<h3>Repair vs Replacement Financial Analysis</h3>
<p>Units over 8 years old with multiple failing thermal components may approach replacement consideration, but our diagnostic approach identifies the most cost-effective repair strategy. We provide honest assessments when repair costs exceed 50% of replacement value, helping you make informed financial decisions. However, most LG dryer overheating issues stem from single component failures that repair economically with years of remaining service life.</p>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3>How quickly can you fix an overheating LG dryer?</h3>
<p>Most LG dryer overheating repairs are completed within 2-3 hours of our technician's arrival, depending on the specific components requiring replacement. We carry common thermal parts on our service trucks for immediate repair. Complex cases requiring special-order parts may need a follow-up visit.</p>
<h3>Is it safe to use my LG dryer if it's overheating?</h3>
<p>Never operate an overheating dryer as this creates serious fire danger and risks permanent damage to expensive internal components. Turn off the unit immediately and unplug it until professional repairs are completed. The thermal protection systems are failing when overheating occurs.</p>
<h3>What causes LG dryers to overheat most commonly?</h3>
<p>Blocked ventilation accounts for about 60% of overheating issues we encounter, followed by failed thermal fuses and faulty high-limit thermostats. Heating element problems and control board malfunctions represent less common but serious causes. Professional diagnosis identifies the specific cause quickly.</p>
<h3>Will my LG dryer warranty cover overheating repairs?</h3>
<p>Manufacturer warranties typically don't cover thermal component failures after the first year, and may be voided by improper ventilation or maintenance. Our repairs include a comprehensive one-year warranty on parts and labor regardless of your dryer's age. We provide protection that manufacturer warranties don't offer.</p>
<h3>How do I prevent my LG dryer from overheating again?</h3>
<p>Regular lint filter cleaning, annual vent system inspection, and proper loading prevent most overheating issues. We provide specific maintenance recommendations based on your installation and usage patterns during our service visit. Call (323) 990-7550 for professional maintenance service that prevents costly emergency repairs.</p>

